  "title": "Mechanical & Electrical (M&E) Coordinator",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate and supervise M&amp;E works including HVAC, plumbing, electrical, fire protection, and other building services.</li>\n  <li>Review M&amp;E drawings, specifications, and schedules to ensure alignment with architectural and structural plans.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with consultants, M&amp;E subcontractors, and suppliers to resolve site and design issues.</li>\n  <li>Monitor progress of M&amp;E works on-site and report to Project Manager regularly.</li>\n  <li>Conduct inspections and ensure compliance with safety, quality, and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Attend coordination meetings and assist in the integration of M&amp;E systems with overall project planning.</li>\n  <li>Track and manage materials, tools, and manpower requirements for M&amp;E installations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper documentation and assist with testing and commissioning processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Mechanical, Electrical, Building Services Engineering, or related field.</li>\n  <li>At least <strong>3–5 years</strong> of experience in M&amp;E coordination in construction or engineering projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of M&amp;E systems, building codes, and safety regulations.</li>\n  <li>Ability to interpret technical drawings and M&amp;E schematics.</li>\n  <li>Good communication and coordination skills to liaise effectively with multiple stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office; AutoCAD or Revit MEP knowledge is a plus.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
